name: Barry
absentee_method: Merged into voters' home precincts and released with cumulative results
nyt_race_description_race: This Republican stronghold in Western Michigan has been trending blue in recent years. With Justin Amash, the conservative incumbent who briefly flirted with a third-party presidential bid, deciding against running for re-election, Democrats see a chance to take the seat with their candidate Hillary Scholten, a former attorney. She is up against Peter Meijer, a businessman and a supermarket scion.
poll_display_race: First polls close at 8 p.m. Eastern time.
